once had a friend we will call him Ted for the post, we were guildmates at the time. I had a twink (now my main) that was a monk, same class as Ted. Ted would log on, say hello group with me was realy cool. Used to send me tells, asking me to trade him my silbisian beserker cloak, would tell me how my twink was better geared then his main and give me a sob story. After weeks of this, I finaly went to him on a guild raid and gave it to him, he cancled the trade window. Asked me what it was for, told him it was for him. He cancled the trade window again, I told him to take it untill he got better, that he realy wanted it and I know he would use it. I stoped hearing from him soon after, a good part because the guild broke up. I would say hello to him from time to time when I saw him on, most of the time I got no response from him. I quit playing EQ for a month, partly because I was severly hampered as a melee class with no haste item now, and repeated tries at camping a replacememt turned up nill. I would ask him from time to time if he had gotten a better cloak yet, as I realy needed that one back. One day he replied with &quot;I'm holding out for one cloak&quot; That being a cloak of the falling stars. Him holding out for a particular cloak did not make me to happy I will say let alone one that falls off the statue in Kael. But as he is in UI, I knew he would eventualy get it. A few weeks later I was grouped with a guildmate of his, and a old friend of both of ours and I had mentioned that they needed to get Ted that cloak, so I could get mine back, and guess what? I was told he got one a while ago. I told them they must be mistaken, as Ted wouldn't do that to me, there was just no way. I was then told to just go up and inspect him, that they knew for sure Ted had one. I was a bit hurt and highly ticked off, those that know me know I have a pretty bad temper, and can say stuff that I don't mean when angry so I didn't log on for a week to cool down. I loged on today to see that Ted was in Sol B, a place I could run in and see for myself, as most places UI hunts I would try to FD flop to. I get to Ted, and sure as hell he has the Cloak of the Falling stars on. I ask him if he sold or traded my cloak. He replied, &quot;is that what you came here for?&quot;. I told him yes, that I had been told he had gotten that cloak some time back and I could not believe that he would do that to me. So he tells me that he still has the cloak in his posesion. I talk to him a bit, and I get all kinds of &quot;excuses&quot; as to why I can't have my cloak back, even though he now has better. His answers are as follows &quot;I've had it too long&quot; (it has been 6-9 months now that he has had my cloak). &quot;You never talk to me anymore less it has to do with the cloak&quot;. Guess that negates the fact I gave you my cloak &quot;Till you got better&quot; and you have been useing it for a damn long time, holding out for a near impos. to get cloak. Not to mention the fact that he never even says hello to me when he logs on, and dosn't bother to respond to tells 90% of the time before I even asked about sometime hopefully sooner then later about receiveing my cloak back. I finaly sent him a tell again before the servers went down, tell was about as follows, /tell Ted I gave you my silbisian beseker cloak untill you got better, you have better now. Are you going to give me my cloak back, or are you going to make excuses to keep it? His response was something like &quot;It is on my girlfriends twink warrior now (we will call the girlfriend Meg to keep it short) and I'm not going to log her on to give you something that is hers. &quot;Something that is hers&quot; I give him a cloak to keep untill he gets better and he gives it to his girlfriends twink, Yea, I'm a bit off the edge now as I felt Meg was a friend too. He also told me we had no deal when I gave it to him, I guess saying &quot;you can have it till ya get better&quot; is no deal, just hit accept on the trade window and pretty much ignore me from then on. Guess the moral of this story is, Don't give stuff to friends till they get better, they will hold out for a near imposs. item to get and prob won't bother to give it back to you if they do get what they want, no matter how bad you need it. I've given away countless items to friends free and clear, this is the only time I've said &quot;till you get better&quot;, some of my friends have given me items back after getting stuff on thier own which I useualy give to others, you rarely see me in EC selling items, I give everything away to peeps I know will use it so can't afford to buy a item anywhere near the calibur of this particular cloak ( for those that know, ac 9, 9 str, stam, agil, dex. +50 hp, 25-30% haste {depending who you listen too, I know mine was faster then a rbg, could see the diff switching them, have had some tell me they parsed it 27-28%} 0.1 wieght. I guess I will close will now by just saying I am realy disapointed and hurt by those I thought were friends and warn you all of the same happening to you. Hope you all get what you are looking for out of your EQ experiance and pardon my piss poor spelling / grammer / english. Take care all!<br><br><br>Tarla Tragic<br>56 monk of E. Marr<br>/shout Monks suck !!! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukavissilversteel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kavis Silversteel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/3/02 4:20:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2856.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sad tail of giving a friend a item &quot;Till he gets be</span><hr size=1> Sad story but have you heard of paragraphs?  Makes reading so much easier. <p></p><