earing a word from you, except that you said you were back to Meg, and she telling me,  You say, &quot;Hi Ted, can I have my cloak back?&quot;.   Then after I said I was still using it, you disappeared about for a few weeks, not saying a word, not even showing up in /who.  <br><br>Then the day finally comes that I got my CoFS.  Were you in /who? no, were you on in a weeks time? no, were you on in a months time? no.  So finally deciding that you quit in my mind, and Yes, I did give my cloak to my girlfriend.  I am not going to against my actions in giving my girlfriend an item just because you decided to come back on a whim, after so long of a time and decide you want to play again.  World doesn't work that way. <br><br>Was it wrong of me? I dunno.  Some might think so, some might not.  I for one falls under the Not half.  You didn't play for over 8 months then come back on and not even saying where you were or anything, asking for the cloak back.  Then disappearing again.  <br><br>You can't give a &quot;friend&quot; a car. Go away for along time, then come back and tell the friend you wrecked your car, and need theirs back now... it won't work.<br><br>I'm sorry that it has to be this way Tarra..<br><br><br>Tedorn Nightshire<br>60 Monk<br>United Independent<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukragarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kragarn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 179<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/3/02 5:44:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2856.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sad tail of giving a friend a item &quot;Till he gets be</span><hr size=1> Ummm Tedorn yes you can in fact give a friend something, leave for an undetermined amount of time and then come back for it.  If in fact you are actually friends.  See that's what true friends actually do.  They help and support each other.<br><br>See how when you had no haste at all and he gave you his cloak.  Now matter which story is true, whether it was until you upgraded or just because he gave it to you, he now has no haste and you have extra haste.  Have you figured out where this is going yet??  When you had none he gave it to you, even if - in fact especially if - he just gave to you with no hope of getting it back, don't you think turn about is fair play???<br><br>I know when one of my true friends in the game returns I check my bank to see what I have that they can use.  And while I won't give them my primary gear, if I have any doubles you can bet they will get them.<br> <p><IMG SRC="http://members.rogers.com/stellarthief/kragarn01.jpg"><br>Rake of the Phoenix Crusaders<br>Ring Warden of EMarr</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utedornnightshire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tedorn Nightshire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/3/02 5:49:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2856.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sad tail of giving a friend a item &quot;Till he gets be</span><hr size=1> Theres a difference from comming back and that same second asking for the cloak, than comming on and see how i'm doing.<br><br><br>friend vs. True friend<br><br>What I thought the be a true friend I guess wasn't Kragarn. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukragarn.showPu