erything* that I loot (which isn't much because I back out of almost everything, unless insisted upon) to friends, or nice people.  I've given locustlores, lamenations etc, for ports to places because loot means nothing (and I normally have no cash on me, being a monk and all).  <br><br>When she started to talk to me again when she returned from her &quot;Absence&quot;, all she wanted was the cloak.  No friendship mattered.  And when I said I couldn't, she said was &quot;Well I guess i'm going to have to make my 1st post on Rant and Flames Emarr board&quot;.   Now shes threatening me about the cloak, and ruining my reputation (if I had one that is).<br><br>Make sense of it how you want. How you view true friends is in the eye of the beholder.<br><br>Ted<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uarryen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arryen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 533<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/3/02 6:52:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2856.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sad tail of giving a friend a item &quot;Till he gets be</span><hr size=1> How you view true friends is completely irrelevant to the fact that it's her cloak, and you're not using it, and you won't give it back.<br><br>You can make it as complicated as you like and still not change that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utedornnightshire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tedorn Nightshire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/3/02 7:01:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFro